Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.50,0:00:07.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}Ran, Sonoko and Sera{, the three of them{（コナン）\N＜蘭・園子・世良の３人は→\N} came across a corpse while headed to school.{found a dead person on their way to school.{登校途中に\Nとある遺体を発見した＞\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.25,0:00:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.50,0:00:14.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Well, he didn't come to work today, so we went looking for him and found him lying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.91,0:00:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}There's blood dripping from his mouth, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.62,0:00:19.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}I called an ambulance just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.74,0:00:23.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}He doesn't need an ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.87,0:00:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}He's already been dead for nine hours, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.06,0:00:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Did he happen to be an alcoholic?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.09,0:00:35.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Uhh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.45,0:00:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Even though he said his doctor told him to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.13,0:00:40.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}But how did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.62,0:00:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}The whites of his eyes have turned yellow, and despite being thin, his belly is bulging out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.15,0:00:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}That's ascites, which proves he had a bad liver.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.90,0:00:57.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Also, a can of beer was left untouched in the delivery bin of the vending machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.29,0:01:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Judging from the situation, it's probably what he was trying to buy just before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.84,0:01:10.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Having drunk alcohol, his cirrhosis caused him to vomit blood from variceal ruptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.24,0:01:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}and at that time, nobody was around to help him, so he ended up dying...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.76,0:01:17.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}That's what you'd normally think.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.56,0:01:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}However, he didn't die from illness...{was TLCed from but->however back in 690 to avoid starting two lines with but, but that never got applied :\}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.45,0:01:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}...but due to a maliciously perpetrated crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.81,0:01:27.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}The proof of that is right in front of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.30,0:01:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.91,0:01:30.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}The character for 'death' was written in blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.72,0:01:34.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}A bloody character proclaiming 'death' was found beside the corpse.{Next to the corpse, [the / a] 'death' character was left written in blood. ＜遺体のそばに残された\N「死」という血文字＞\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.52,0:01:43.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}It resembled one from ten years ago, in the one case where my father, Yūsaku Kudō, never revealed the perpetrator.{[had] faced a similar crime where [he/they] never specified who was behind it.唯一　犯人を指定しなかった事件に\N酷似していた＞\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.79,0:01:49.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}To look for similarities between the two cases,{[In order] to explore the similarities between the two cases{＜２つの事件の\N共通点を探るべく→\N} we called Detective Takagi, who led the investigation.{we called Detective Takagi, who took part [in the investigation]...担当である高木刑事に\N電話してみると…＞\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.33,0:01:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Ah, the corpse this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.84,0:01:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}I don't know what happened to the corpse afterwards though.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.05,0:02:00.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Since it was a theft case, the investigation was handed over to Division Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.26,0:02:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}T-Theft? Wasn't it a murder case?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.90,0:02:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Hey, quit fooling around! How is it a theft case?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.96,0:02:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Didn't you see that bloody 'death' character too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.47,0:02:13.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Y-Yeah, I thought the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.78,0:02:16.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}'Perhaps this is some bizarre murder.'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.83,0:02:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}But Inspector Megure, who passed you girls as you headed off to school,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.69,0:02:25.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}said 'This must've been theft...'\N the moment he saw that bloody character...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.75,0:02:29.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}Not a murder case, but a theft?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.29,0:02:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Isn't it strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.06,0:02:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}I'm sure Inspector Megure was the lead\N investigator for the case ten years ago too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.20,0:02:39.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}It wouldn't be odd for him to think it was the work of a serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.84,0:02:42.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}She has a point...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.55,0:02:49.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}Ten years ago, Inspector Megure had his eyes fixated on that bloody character, so why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.98,0:02:56.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}And back then, didn't Dad say something to the kid who was the first {person }to discover the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.01,0:02:57.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}And he did it with a smile...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.57,0:03:01.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}How?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.24,0:03:04.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}How did he decide it wasn't a murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.35,0:03:07.40,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}How?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.52,0:03:10.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}{\blur2}It doesn't matter how many times you try,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.24,0:03:12.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}{\blur2}whether it's in love, cases, today, or tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.10,0:03:15.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}The mystery behind the character connected with Dad's cold case!{that The mystery behind the character\Nthat was shared with dad's unsolved case!＜父さん　未解決　あの事件\N 共通する文字の謎！＞\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.85,0:03:17.36,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}{\blur2}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.36,0:03:19.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}{\blur2}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.02,0:03:22.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}{\blur2}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.44,0:05:14.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Perhaps he knew who the killer was, but the police forced him to stay silent?{Could it be that the police had found someone related to them（世良）\Nまさか　犯人がわかってるのに→\N}{ was behind the case, but chose to hide it?{警察ぐるみで\N隠蔽してるんじゃないか？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.74,0:05:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}N-No way!{C-Could that possibly mean...?!{（園子）そ　それってまさか！？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.25,0:05:18.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}You couldn't mean that the son of some police bigshot{It frequently happens in movies and drama shows,映画やドラマでよくある→\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.74,0:05:21.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}or important businessman did it,\N and even though they hate the thought,{that because the culprit is someone belonging to the upper echelons of police hierarchy犯人が警察の上層部や政財界の\N御曹司だから→\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.75,0:05:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}the police can't lay a hand on him, like you see all the time in movies and dramas?!{null.AR: added "don't pursue" so that the phrase makes sense}{they [don't pursue] the despicable bastard who was behind it?!憎たらしいけど\N手が出せないってヤツね！？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.13,0:05:28.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}Look who's talking. You're a child of the Suzuki Financial Group yourself...{So says a girl{[And you're supposed to be / So says] a lady from the Suzuki Financial Group...《そういうオメーも鈴木財閥の\Nお嬢様だろうが》\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.67,0:05:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}I don't think Shin'ichi's dad would back off from\N a case just because of something like that though.{However, I don't think Shin'ichi's dad would back off from a case because of something like that.でもさあ\N新一のお父さんが→\N そんな理由で事件から\N手を引くとは思えないけど。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.99,0:05:37.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Y-Yeah, that's true...{そ　それもそうね。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.26,0:05:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Then why don't we try asking him?{Why don't we try consulting him if that's the case?{（沖矢）だったら　相談してみては\Nいかがですか？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.05,0:05:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}You can ask Kin'ichi-{\i1}kun{\i0}, that\N deduction-loving classmate of yours.{That guy who likes mysteries and is your classmate, Kin'ichi-kun.推理好きの君のクラスメート\N金一君に。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.30,0:05:46.40,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}Kin'ichi...?{《えっ　金一？》\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.91,0:05:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}I guess you're right.{えっ　ああ…\Nそ　そうですね。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.15,0:05:52.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Huh? What're you talking about?{（世良）\Nはあ？なに言ってんだよ？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.49,0:05:56.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}If we're gonna ask anyone about the case, it should be Shin'ichi Kudō-{\i1}kun{\i0}, right?{The one we should consult about the case is Shin'ichi Kudō, right?事件のこと相談するなら工藤新一君だろ？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.10,0:05:58.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Because he's a high-school detective and your boyfriend.{高校生探偵で\N君の彼氏なんだから。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.15,0:06:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Though I guess he's not living here at the \Nmoment because he's off chasing some case.{And it seems he vacated this house due to being investigating a case right now.今は何かの事件を追ってて\Nこの家を空けてるみたいだけどな。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.71,0:06:10.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Oh... So this house belongs to that high-school detective?{ほぉ～　この家の家主は\Nあの高校生探偵でしたか。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.46,0:06:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Don't tell me you've been living here\N without even knowing that...?{え？まさかあんた→\N そんなことも知らずにここに住んでたのか？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.73,0:06:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Right. Ran-{\i1}san{\i0} said that the Shin'ichi-{\i1}kun{\i0} living here was just an ordinary high-school student.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.64,0:06:31.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Also,{Besides,それに} there are rumours around saying that the high-school detective Shin'ichi Kudō{There have been rumors flying around saying that high-school detective, Shin'ichi Kudō,　風の噂で\N高校生探偵の工藤新一は→\N} lost his life investigating a case,{lost his life while he was investigating a case事件の捜査中に命を落として→\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.55,0:06:34.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}and vanished from the world of mystery-solving.{because [I] heard he had disappeared from the mystery-solving scene.{謎解きの舞台から\N消えたと聞いていましたから。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.49,0:06:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}P-People are really spreading rumours like that?!{Th-There're rumours such as that running about?{そ　そんな噂に\Nなってるんですか？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.07,0:06:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Yeah. That's why I thought the Shin'ichi-{\i1}kun{\i0} you kept talking of was somebody else.{Yeah. That's why, when I heard you repeatedly mentioning [the name of] 'Shin'ichi-kun', I figured you were talking about somebody else. {ええ　なので　君たちの会話に度々出てくる新一君とは→\N\N別人だと。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.28,0:06:45.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}But he isn't dead, right?{死んでるわけないだろ？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.12,0:06:49.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}I've worked on the same case as him twice.{Because he and I have [both] been involved in two cases.{僕は　二度も彼と同じ事件にかかわってるんだからさ。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.81,0:06:52.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Though both times it was just over the phone.{Well, even though both times he was just on the other side of a phone.まあ\N二度とも電話だったけどな。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.05,0:06:55.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Isn't that right, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?{ん？\Nだよな？コナン君。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.29,0:06:57.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Uh, yeah... That's right...{あっ　うん　そうだね\Nアハ　ハハハハ…。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.78,0:07:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Then who is Kin'ichi...?{Then, that 'Kin'ichi' you mentioned [is / was]...?{では　金一というのは？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.47,0:07:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Ah, well...{Ah, [about / regarding] that...{ああ　それは…\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.40,0:07:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Shin'ichi told me not to tell you too much about him, so I improvised...{I just said that because Shin'ichi didn't want me to talk too much about him around you... 新一が昴さんに→\N\Nあまり自分のことを話すなと言ってたので　つい…。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.81,0:07:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}I'm sorry{ [for that]}...{ご　ごめんなさい。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.73,0:07:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}But why are there rumours about Shin'ichi-{\i1}kun{\i0} being dead?{But I wonder why there was that rumour going around about Shin'ichi-kun having died...{でも　なんで新一君　死んだなんて\N噂になってるんだろうね？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.66,0:07:23.41,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,{\blur1}That's probably because he always insists that everyone{I'm sure that was becauseそれはきっと→\N}{ he's always getting himself involved with casesいつも事件の関係者に\N自分がかかわったことを→\N} involved in cases with him should keep his involvement hidden.{but doesn't want his interventions to be [made public / widely known / known].伏せるように　しつこく\N言ってるからじゃないかなあ。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.41,0:07:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Almost as if he doesn't want to alarm the culprit of the case he's on...{Perhaps it's because he doesn't want to be chased by the criminals he has [helped apprehend / apprehended].なんか　追ってる事件の犯人に\N警戒されないためみたいだけど。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.28,0:07:32.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}What, is he some sort of ninja \Ninfiltrating the enemy fortress?{As if he was [some kind of / a] ninja hiding inside the enemy [castle / stronghold / fortress]...あやつは敵の城に潜伏してる\N忍者かっつ～の。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.29,0:07:34.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\blur2}A ninja...?{忍者…。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.63,0:07:38.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}Then why don't we call him right now?{Then, how about we we give him a call right now?じゃあ　今から\N電話してみるのはどうだ？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.84,0:07:41.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}I'd like to hear him figure it out too.{I'd like to hear his reasoning too.僕も彼の推理　聞きたいし。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.42,0:07:42.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}{ああ}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.00,0:07:45.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\blur1}B-But I already sent him an e-mail outlining the case earlier in the evening.{B-But　で　でも}{ we already sent him an e-mail with the case's details this evening.　事件の概要は夕方　メールで伝えたし。\N}
